<ue5><m0>Eleven arrested, four cops hurt<ql>
in downtown riot at tourist site<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0>   <m0>QUEBEC<m0> (--) Cars were damaged and windows broken early Saturday in a three-hour riot touched off when police tried to arrest several people for setting a fire in a street in the city's historic Old Town, a popular tourist area.<ep>
   Police used tear gas and fired pepper spray into the rioters several hours after the trouble began, said police spokesman Jean Eudes Lachance. Eleven people were arrested and four police officers were injured, most with cuts from being hit with rocks and bottles.<ep>
   Another police spokesman said the trouble began when police tried to break up a crowd of about 1,500 young people who had set a large fire in the street. Police tried to arrest several of the youths but the crowd responded by throwing rocks at the officers.<ql>
