<ue5><m0>Author: Mowat's research<ql>
into Inuits, wolves is fiction<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0>   In the latest issue of Saturday Night magazine, journalist John Goddard says Farley Mowat did not conduct the Arctic research he described in his books <m0>Never Cry Wolf, People of the Deer  <m0>and <m0>The Desperate People.<m0><ep>
   Goddard's heavily document article includes assertions that Mowat:<ep>
   (box) Did not spend two years in the Keewatin District of the Far North, as his books say, but was there for less than six months.<ep>
   (box) Never set foot in an Inuit camp and did not once see a starving Inuit person.<ep>
   (box) Spent only 90 hours over a period of less than four weeks studying wolves and did not live with the wolves but commuted daily from a cabin he shared with another man.<ep>
   Mowat, 74, replied Saturday: ``For a guy who is sanctimoniously devoted to facts, this guy's got . . . as many facts wrong as there are flies on a toad that's road kill.''<ql>
