<ue5><m0>Teen `terrorist' is charged<ql>
in rape, pellet-gun shootings<ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0>   <m0>HAMILTON<m0> (--) A 15-year-old boy has been charged with more than 20 serious crimes, including the rape of a 14-year-old girl.<ep>
   ``This is a little terrorist,'' police Sgt. Dennis Waddle said.<ep>
   The boy is charged with attacking six girls ages 13 to 15. One of them was raped. The others were injured by shots fired from a pellet gun. The three-month string of crimes terrorized residents of an east Hamilton apartment building.<ep>
   The boy is charged with four counts of assault with a weapon, breaking and entering, and theft. Other charges include sexual assault, forcible confinement, careless use of a firearm, possession of a dangerous weapon, assault and mischief. A second 15-year-old boy, who allegedly kept the rape victim from escaping, is charged with sexual assault and forcible confinement.<ql>
